  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of WASH Services to Afghan Refugees in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ICMC initiated a project which aims to provide refugees in Munda Camp with access to safe drinking water, improved sanitation, and enhanced awareness of hygiene practices to reduce the prevalence of water-borne diseases. The project also includes strengthening the capacity of local authorities to ensure the provision of sustainable water and sanitation services.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The activities include:
- the construction of communal hand pumps, latrines, and waste disposal points;
- the rehabilitation of the drainage system within the camp;
- the provision of trainings on rehabilitation and maintenance of the WASH infrastructure;
- the organisation of awareness raising sessions on various topics including health and hygiene, safe water handling, latrine use and maintenance, personal hygiene, environmental sanitation and solid waste management; 
- the formation of a project steering committee with representation of Government Offices, UN organizations and I/NGOs;
- the provision of training to local service providers-officials of Government offices and WASH committee members on effective planning, designing, implementation and management of the WASH related interventions.</narrative>
  </description>
